HEADWORD: Woodenness
<hw>Wood"en*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Quality of being wooden;
clumsiness; stupidity; blockishness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We set our faces against the <qex>woodenness</qex> which then
characterized German philology.</q> <rj><qau>Sweet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wood gum</ent>⟦br⟧
